Dating: GRAECO-ROMAN PERIOD (not before); LATE PERIOD; LATE PERIOD (not after)
Name: Cartonnage of a mummy
Description: Cartonnage of a mummy, with two jackals drawn on it. The jackals, symbol of Anubis, are shown facing each other and sitting down over two naos with cornice and lock. Between them, the inscription mentions the god with his epithet of lord of the sacred land, referring to the necropolis.
